# Formatting After Edits

After editing any file, ensure it conforms to the project's formatters. Run the appropriate formatter before considering the task complete.

## Formatters by File Type

| File Type | Formatter | Command |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| `*.gd` (GDScript) | gdformat | `gdformat path/to/file.gd` |
| `*.py` | black (or project default) | `black path/to/file.py` |
| `*.json` | Prettier (if configured) | `npx prettier --write path/to/file.json` |

## GDScript (gdtoolkit)

Install: `pip install gdtoolkit`. This provides `gdformat`, `gdlint`, etc. (add Python Scripts to PATH if needed).

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `gdformat path/to/file.gd` | Format GDScript |
| `gdformat file1.gd file2.gd` | Format multiple files |
| `gdlint path/to/file.gd` | Lint GDScript |

Run `gdformat` after editing `.gd` files.

## Workspace Settings

